    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Septr 18th 1853</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I regret extremely that I<lb/> should have understood your favor to
                me<lb/> to have meant that I should have had<lb/> the pleasure of seeing you in the
                city<lb/> last <date>Thursday</date> but on reperusal I find<lb/> that you meant
                that you would be in<lb/> town (meaning <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>) this
                I<lb/> trust will explain my not answering you<lb/> before for I must be candid
                enough to<lb/> confess to you that it takes some little<lb/> trouble to decipher
                your epistles I regret<lb/> extremely that you should have imagined<lb/> that I
                should have written anything<lb/> to attack you or your paper for without<lb/> being
                guilty of any flattery I would<lb/> state to you that I have always looked<lb/> upon
                you as an ornament to our faith<lb/> and although I might at <sic>time</sic>
                have<lb/> thought differently from some ideas<lb/> you may have put forth yet I
                have<lb/> always considered your abilities so<lb/> much superior to mine that I
                have<lb/> thought you may have been right<lb/> and knowing at the same time they
                were</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>honestly advocated. In relation to the<lb/> article in the Asmonean in reply to<lb/>
                yours I would state that some of the<lb/> gentlemen composing the committee<lb/>
                appointed for the purpose of procuring<lb/> funds for the destitute in
                    <placeName>New Orleans</placeName><lb/> observing the article in your paper<lb/>
                thought that it would have the effect<lb/> of preventing persons to subscribe to
                the<lb/> destitute in <placeName>New Orleans</placeName> and for this<lb/> purpose
                they requested me to reply in<lb/> the Asmonean that being a weekly<lb/> publication
                the bad effects of your<lb/> article would not have so much effect<lb/> I should not
                have written the article<lb/> had I imagined it to have been the<lb/> slightest
                source of vexation to you<lb/> but believing that you had correspondents<lb/> in the
                city of <placeName>New Orleans</placeName> and that your<lb/> article was written
                prior to your going<lb/> to press that you <sic>was</sic> not posted up<lb/>
                properly on the subject or had not your<lb/> servers attention drawn to the
                unfortunate<lb/> position of <placeName>New Orleans</placeName> and the
                adjacent<lb/> cities I shall <sic>allways</sic> feel pleasure<lb/> in writing to you
                any news that may<lb/> interest you or your readers in the city<lb/> of
                    <placeName>Mobile</placeName> in relation to my remarks<lb/> upon the subject of
                    <placeName>China</placeName> I have<lb/> always thought with you that a <hi
                    rend="underline">general</hi><lb/> move ought to be made by our first</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>my dear sir that cup does not fit you<lb/> I should be very happy to meet you<lb/>
                prior to my return to <placeName>Mobile</placeName> which will<lb/> not be until the
                yellow fever terminates<lb/> should you visit <placeName>New York</placeName> I
                should<lb/> have pleasure in calling on you or<lb/> should I go by way of
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> I shall take the liberty of seeing
                you</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Joseph Morrison</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
